# Commit message format

**Note:** The Source Control **Generate Commit Message** button reads `.cursorrules` in the repo root, not this file. Keep both in sync.

When generating git commit messages for this repo, always use this structure:

```
v{VERSION} - {Short summary of changes}
- {Descriptive bullet about a config or other change.}
- {Another bullet. Start with verbs: Adjusted, Increased, Updated, Modified, Added, Introduced, Removed, etc.}
- ...

➕ Dodane mody:
- {ModName} v{version}
- ...

✔️ Zaktualizowane mody:
- {ModName} (v{oldVersion} ➡️ v{newVersion})
- ...

➖ Usuniete mody:
- {ModName} (v{version})
- ...
```

## Rules

1. **Title**: `v{VERSION} - ...` — bump patch version from the previous commit (e.g. v1.1.1 → v1.1.2). Check `git log -1` for the current version.
2. **Body bullets**: Describe config changes and other non-mod changes. Be specific (setting names, old → new values when relevant). No blank line between title and first bullet.
3. **➕ Dodane mody**: Include only when new plugin folders were added under `BepInEx/plugins/`. Omit if none added.
4. **✔️ Zaktualizowane mody**: Include only when existing plugin folders changed version. Format: `{NAZWA} (v{stara} ➡️ v{nowa})`. Omit if none updated.
5. **➖ Usuniete mody**: Include only when plugin folders were removed under `BepInEx/plugins/`. Format: `{NAZWA} (v{wersja})`. Omit if none removed.
6. **Mod line format**: `{NAZWA} v{WERSJA}` — parse from folder name `autor-nazwaModa-wersja`; replace underscores with spaces in the name. If the folder has no version, read `version_number` from `manifest.json`.
7. **Auto-release**: Po pushu na `main` commit z tytulem `vX.Y.Z - ...` GitHub Actions automatycznie tworzy `release.zip` i publikuje GitHub Release z tagiem `vX.Y.Z`.

## Example

```
v1.1.2 - Update configuration files for various plugins
- Adjusted window position in ConfigurationManager settings.
- Increased container range in AzuCraftyBoxes configuration from 20 to 25.
- Updated build range increase per upgrade in CraftingStationTweakz from 4 to 10.
- Modified backpack weight setting from 85 to 65.
- Added new configuration files for Eternal Fire and Shared Map Pins plugins.
- Introduced new settings for the Valheim Clock and Venture Floating Items plugins.
- Updated various existing configuration files for better compatibility and performance.

➕ Dodane mody:
- Eternal Fire v1.0.17
- Jam v1.1.0
- MinimalStatusEffects v1.0.7
- Venture Floating Items v0.3.3
- SharedMapPins v1.1.0
- ValheimClock v1.5.2

✔️ Zaktualizowane mody:
- Eternal Fire (v1.0.16 ➡️ v1.0.17)

➖ Usuniete mody:
- Epic Loot (v1.2.2)
```
